The article consists of statements from various members of Congress, media personalities, and commentators expressing their support for President Trump's tough stance on China in trade negotiations. Many of them believe that China has not been negotiating in good faith and that the US needs to stand strong in order to secure real changes in trade. They argue that China's unfair trade practices have hurt American workers and that tariffs are necessary to level the playing field. The commentators also praise Trump for taking aggressive action against China and protecting the US economy.